- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for representing hypergeometric products and indefinite nested sums in a difference ring, which involves symbolic manipulation.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses new algorithms for representing hypergeometric products.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper deals with solving the zero-recognition problem for hypergeometric products.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper may involve analyzing the computational complexity of the algorithms proposed.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a less likely category, but it is possible that the algorithms proposed in the paper could have applications in game theory.
